# PlatformIO Private Libraries

This directory is intended for project-specific (private) libraries.

PlatformIO will compile these libraries into static libraries and link them into the final executable file.

Each library should be placed in its own directory using the following structure:

```text
lib/
├── YourLibrary/
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── YourLibrary.cpp
│   │   └── YourLibrary.h
│   ├── examples/
│   ├── docs/
│   └── library.json   # Optional
```

Example project structure:

```text
├── lib
│   ├── Bar
│   │   ├── docs
│   │   ├── examples
│   │   ├── src
│   │   │   ├── Bar.c
│   │   │   └── Bar.h
│   │   └── library.json
│   │
│   ├── Foo
│   │   ├── Foo.c
│   │   └── Foo.h
│   │
│   └── README.md
│
├── platformio.ini
└── src
    └── main.c
```

Example usage in `src/main.c`:

```c
#include <Foo.h>
#include <Bar.h>

int main(void)
{
    // Your code here
    return 0;
}
```

PlatformIO's Library Dependency Finder (LDF) automatically detects dependent libraries by scanning project source files.

More information:
- https://docs.platformio.org/page/librarymanager/ldf.html
- https://docs.platformio.org/page/librarymanager/config.html